<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFD1FFF0A5CDFC671BAEFB13" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5CDFC671D33FC18" blockId="33.[136,780,957,984]" box="[136,780,957,984]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFD1FFF0A5CDFC671D33FC18" box="[136,780,957,984]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="4">
11.1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A583FC641C60FC18" authority="Kunth (1817: 276)" authorityName="Kunth" authorityPageNumber="276" authorityYear="1817" box="[198,607,957,984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A583FC641FBAFC18" bold="true" box="[198,389,957,984]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Verbena litoralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A4C9FC641C60FC18" author="Kunth, C. S." box="[396,607,957,984]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="244 - 285" refId="ref35065" refString="Kunth, C. S. (1817) [1818] Verbenaceae. In: Humboldt, F., Bonpland, A. &amp; Kunth, C. S. (Eds.) Nova Genera et Species Plantarum (quarto ed.) 2. Lutetiae Parisiorum, Paris pp. 244 - 285." type="book chapter" year="1817">Kunth (1817: 276)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (Figs. 3B, 7H)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5CDFBDC1BAEFB13" blockId="33.[136,1452,1029,1884]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Herbs 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A591FBDC1F78FBE0" box="[212,327,1029,1056]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="0.95" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4‒1.5 m</quantity>
high, branches tetragonal, glabrescent. Leaves opposite, blade 3.3‒4.3 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A1D4FBDF1B2CFBE0" box="[1169,1299,1030,1056]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="cm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.1">1.1‒1.3 cm</quantity>
, chartaceous, oval-elliptical to oblong, apex acute to obtuse, base cuneate, margin entire up to the third middle, dentate-serrate toward the apex, ciliate, strigose on both surfaces, trichomes concentrated along the veins. Inflorescences 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A012FB971E95FB4C" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="cm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.8">2.8‒3.4 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle of the main spikes 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A77AFBAB1C81FB4C" box="[575,702,1138,1164]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="2.3">2.3‒3.7 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle of the lateral spikes 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A127FBA81ADEFB4C" box="[1122,1249,1137,1164]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="cm" value="4.8" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.5">4.5‒5.1 cm</quantity>
long, glabrous to puberulous; bracts 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A425FB4F1F80FB70" box="[352,447,1174,1200]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2‒3 mm</quantity>
long, oval-lanceolate, abaxial surface glabrescent, margin ciliate; calyx 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A1B2FB4F1B55FB70" box="[1271,1386,1174,1200]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="3.0">3‒3.1 mm</quantity>
long, externally strigose; corolla 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A4FFFB631C13FB14" box="[442,556,1210,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="3.6" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.2">3.2‒4 mm</quantity>
long, pink or lilac. Fruit 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A600FB631D59FB13" box="[837,870,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFD1FFF0A628FB601DFCFB14" box="[877,963,1209,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, surrounded by the persistent calyx.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFD1FFF0A5F8FB041C9CF89C" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5F8FB041F13FA6B" blockId="33.[136,1452,1029,1884]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5F8FB041C3FFB37" bold="true" box="[189,512,1245,1272]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A745FB041C86FB37" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[512,697,1245,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A745FB041C86FB37" box="[512,697,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Verbena litoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed throughout 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A68BFB041A7FFB37" box="[974,1088,1245,1271]" name="Argentina" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A10CFB041AAFFB37" box="[1097,1168,1245,1271]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A1DDFB041AD2FB37" box="[1176,1261,1245,1271]" name="Bolivia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A1B3FB041B0AFB37" box="[1270,1333,1245,1271]" name="Chile" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Chile</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A07BFB071B98FB38" box="[1342,1447,1246,1272]" name="Paraguay" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A5CDFADB1ED4FADC" box="[136,235,1282,1308]" name="Uruguay" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A5B2FADB1F12FADC" box="[247,301,1282,1308]" name="Peru" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A47DFAD81F96FADB" box="[312,425,1281,1307]" name="Colombia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A4F0FAD81C14FADB" box="[437,555,1281,1307]" name="Venezuela" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A773FAD81C99FADB" box="[566,678,1281,1307]" name="Honduras" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A7A4FAD81D08FADB" box="[737,823,1281,1307]" name="Mexico" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A6E8FADB1DD9FADB" box="[941,998,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2007). It is considered a ruderal species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A5D5FAFC1F17FA80" author="Lorenzi, H." box="[144,296,1317,1344]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref35241" refString="Lorenzi, H. (1991) Plantas daninhas do Brasil: terrestres, aquaticas, parasitas, toxicas e medicinais. Instituto Plantarum, Nova Odessa, 440 pp." type="book" year="1991">Lorenzi 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and is found in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A4A7FAFC1C19FAFF" box="[482,550,1317,1343]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
throughout the states of 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A67DFAFC1DE5FA80" box="[824,986,1317,1344]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A6A1FAFC1A43FAFF" box="[996,1148,1317,1343]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A1C2FAFC1B15FAFF" box="[1159,1322,1317,1343]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A071FAFF1B97FAFF" box="[1332,1448,1317,1344]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A5CDFA931EE8FAA4" box="[136,215,1354,1380]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A5A1FA931FB2FAA3" box="[228,397,1353,1380]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A4DCFA901C50FAA3" box="[409,623,1353,1379]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(O’Leary 2020), and Distrito Federal (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A168FA901B20FAA4" author="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Dias, A. M. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Ferreira, S. C. &amp; Silva, T. R. S." box="[1069,1311,1353,1380]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="83 - 132" refId="ref37997" refString="Salimena, F. R. G., Dias, A. M., Mulgura, M. E., Ferreira, S. C. &amp; Silva, T. R. S. (2015) Verbenaceae. In: Cavalcante, T. B. &amp; Amaral-Lopes, A. C. (Eds.) Flora do Distrito Federal, Brasil. Vol. 12, 1 ed. Embrapa, Brasilia, pp. 83 - 132." type="book chapter" year="2015">
Salimena 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A1E5FA931AEDFAA3" box="[1184,1234,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A016FA901EF4FA48" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, this species occurs in disturbed areas of dense rainforest. It was found in a SPA of this state: Parque Estadual do Forno Grande.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5F8FA6F1A9CFA0F" blockId="33.[136,1452,1029,1884]" box="[189,1187,1461,1488]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5F8FA6F1F60FA10" bold="true" box="[189,351,1462,1488]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Collected with flowers and fruits in April, July, September, and December.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5F8FA001B20F9D8" blockId="33.[136,1452,1029,1884]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5F8FA001CBDFA34" bold="true" box="[189,642,1497,1524]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Preliminary conservation assessment:</emphasis>
—This is a common species (ruderal) with a wide distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A017FA001EFDF9D8" author="Lorenzi, H." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref35241" refString="Lorenzi, H. (1991) Plantas daninhas do Brasil: terrestres, aquaticas, parasitas, toxicas e medicinais. Instituto Plantarum, Nova Odessa, 440 pp." type="book" year="1991">Lorenzi 1991</bibRefCitation>
